@node "history" "TrueReality - History"

 990629.3 -011114
          -Added preliminary software lighting code since MiniGL doesn't support lighting.
           This makes Mario look almost ok in the intro to Mario 64.
          -Disabled the FPS counter in window mode for stability reasons.
          -Pressing the HELP key will now save a screenshot in ppm format.
          -040124
          -Recompiled using latest MiniGL (v1.2) and newer GCC (2.95.3 vs 2.95.2).

 990629.2 -000120
          -Some small fixes to this old version. There is actually a newer version of TR out,
           but since the static compiler isn't complete, there is no reason to update the Amiga
           version to that release. I've also ditched the 2D and J3D versions, after all, the
           N64 is a 3D consol, and no one likes playing a 3D game in wireframe!
          -The Mario64 logo is now visible after fixing an Amiga specific bug.
          -000123
          -Major graphical improvements. Mario 64 now looks a lot better!

 990629.3 -000324
          -Compiled a MiniGL version, this is faster but currently the 2D stuff isn't working
           making it quite useless.
          -000325
          -Added -screen (fullscreen) and -width options.
          -000326
          -Some minor changes to the AmigaOS code, -nofps option added.
          -000410
          -Recompiled with EGCS 2.95.2.
          -Fixed the Mario64 logo.
          -Removed a crash, the problem with MiniGL is that it ("thanks" to CyberGraphics)
           crashes if a printf (or similar) is executed when in hardware locked state.
          -I just watched Mario64 at 3-4fps on my 603e'200. Much faster and much better
           gfx quality than using StormMESA IMHO, there are still some problems with the gfx,
           Mario himself look a bit weird for example.



@endnode
